name: Cable Incline Fly (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Set up a stability ball at an incline angle. | Step:2 Attach the cable handles to the high pulleys of a cable machine. | Step:3 Sit on the stability ball facing away from the machine, with your feet firmly planted on the ground. | Step:4 Grasp the cable handles with an overhand grip, palms facing forward. | Step:5 Lean forward slightly, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:6 With a controlled motion, bring your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:7 Continue the motion until your arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:8 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and place a resistance band around your ankles. | Step:2 Take a big step forward with your right foot and a smaller step back with your left foot. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lower your body until your right thigh is parallel to the ground, keeping your left knee slightly above the ground. | Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side.

name: Targeted Style Single Leg Calf Raise (On A Dumbbell)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Lift one foot off the ground and balance on the other foot. | Step:3 Slowly raise your heel as high as possible, using your calf muscles. Emphasize targeted control. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Stability Style Band Kneeling One Arm Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a sturdy anchor point above your head. | Step:2 Kneel down and hold the band with one hand, palm facing down. | Step:3 Extend your arm fully overhead, keeping your elbow slightly bent. | Step:4 Engage your lat muscles and pull the band down towards your side, bringing your elbow towards your ribcage. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides. Perform with stability intensity.

name: Balance Cable Incline Fly
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a low position and attach the handles. | Step:2 Sit on an incline bench with your back against the pad and feet flat on the floor. Perform with balance intensity. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and extend your arms straight out in front of you. | Step:4 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, open your arms out to the sides in a controlled motion. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Hyperextension (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself face down on a stability ball with your hips resting on the ball and your feet against a wall for stability. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head or cross them over your chest. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly lift your upper body off the ball, extending your back until your body forms a straight line. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back. | Step:2 Take a large step forward with one leg, keeping your torso upright. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your front knee and hip, while keeping your back leg straight. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your front thigh is parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then push through your front heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Single Leg Calf Raise (On A Dumbbell)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Lift one foot off the ground and balance on the other foot. | Step:3 Slowly raise your heel as high as possible, using your calf muscles. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Band One Arm Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and place a resistance band around your ankles. | Step:2 Extend one leg forward and rest the top of your foot on a bench or step behind you. | Step:3 Hold onto a support with one hand for balance. | Step:4 Bend your standing leg and lower your body down into a squat position, keeping your knee in line with your toes. | Step:5 Push through your heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Exercise Ball Back Extension With Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying face down on the stability ball with your hips resting on the ball and your feet firmly planted on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head or cross them over your chest. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly lift your upper body off the ball, extending your back until your body forms a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly rotate your torso to one side, keeping your hips and legs stable. | Step:5 Return to the center and repeat the rotation to the other side. | Step:6 Lower your upper body back down to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Squat On Bosu Ball
instructions: Step:1 Place the bosu ball on the ground with the flat side up. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and position yourself on top of the bosu ball. | Step:3 Lower your body down by bending your knees and hips, as if sitting back into a chair. | Step:4 Keep your chest up and your weight on your heels. | Step:5 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Russian Twists (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands and extend your arms straight out in front of you. | Step:3 Lean back slightly while keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Twist your torso to the right, bringing the cable handle towards your right hip. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then twist your torso to the left, bringing the cable handle towards your left hip. | Step:6 Continue alternating twists for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Back Extension With Arms Extended
instructions: Step:1 Place the stability ball on the ground and lie face down on top of it, with your hips resting on the ball and your feet against a wall for stability. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out in front of you, with your palms facing down. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly lift your upper body off the ball, keeping your back straight and your neck in line with your spine. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Back Extension With Hands Behind Head
instructions: Step:1 Place the stability ball on the ground and lie face down on top of it with your hips resting on the ball. | Step:2 Position your feet against a wall or other stable surface for support. | Step:3 Cross your arms behind your head, with your hands touching the back of your head. | Step:4 Engage your core and slowly lift your upper body off the ball, extending your back until your body forms a straight line from your head to your hips. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Take a step forward with one foot and position your feet so that your front foot is flat on the ground and your back foot is elevated on a bench or step. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your front knee and hip, keeping your back knee slightly bent and your back heel off the ground. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your front thigh is parallel to the ground, then push through your front heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Exercise Ball One Legged Diagonal Kick Hamstring Curl
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your back with your legs extended and your heels resting on top of the stability ball. | Step:2 Place your arms by your sides for stability. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and core muscles to lift your hips off the ground, creating a straight line from your shoulders to your heels. | Step:4 Bend your right knee and bring it towards your chest, keeping your left leg extended and your foot flexed. | Step:5 Kick your right leg diagonally across your body, extending it fully and engaging your hamstrings. | Step:6 Slowly return your right leg to the starting position, maintaining control and stability. | Step:7 Repeat the movement with your left leg, alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Single Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a barbell in front of your thighs with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Shift your weight onto your left foot and lift your right foot slightly off the ground. | Step:3 Hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your right leg extended behind you for balance. | Step:4 Lower the barbell towards the ground, keeping it close to your body and your left leg slightly bent. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift your torso back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Extend one leg forward and keep it off the ground throughout the exercise. | Step:3 Bend your standing leg and lower your body down as if sitting back into a chair. | Step:4 Keep your chest up and your back straight. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl V Sit On Bosu Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bosu ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward and your arms fully extended down by your sides. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand. | Step:2 Shift your weight onto your left leg and lift your right foot slightly off the ground. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, hinge forward at the hips and lower the dumbbell towards the ground. | Step:4 At the same time, extend your right leg straight behind you, maintaining a slight bend in your left knee. | Step:5 Lower the dumbbell until your torso and right leg are parallel to the ground. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then engage your glutes and hamstrings to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Reverse Hyper Extension (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a stability ball with your hips resting on the ball and your legs extended straight behind you. | Step:2 Place your hands on the ground in front of you for stability. | Step:3 Engaging your glutes and hamstrings, lift your legs up towards the ceiling as high as you can. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Back Extension With Knees Off Ground
instructions: Step:1 Place the stability ball on the ground and lie face down on top of it, with your hips resting on the ball and your feet against a wall for stability. | Step:2 Position your hands behind your head or crossed over your chest. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly lift your upper body off the ball, extending your back until your body forms a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Back Extension On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Place the stability ball on the ground and lie face down on top of it, with your hips resting on the ball and your feet against a wall or other stable surface. | Step:2 Position your hands behind your head or crossed over your chest. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly lift your upper body off the ball, extending your back until your body forms a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the smith machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Place one foot behind you on a bench or step, with your toes pointing forward. | Step:3 Hold onto the smith machine bar for stability. | Step:4 Bend your front knee and lower your body down into a lunge position, keeping your back straight. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your front heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Ankle Circles
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Lift one leg off the ground and rotate your ankle in a circular motion. | Step:3 Perform the desired number of circles in one direction, then switch to the other direction. | Step:4 Repeat with the other leg.

name: Half Sit-Up (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Leg Hip Raise (Leg Straight)
instructions: Step:1 Lie on an incline bench with your back flat against the bench and your legs extended straight out in front of you. | Step:2 Place your hands on the sides of the bench for support. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your legs off the bench, raising them as high as you can while keeping them straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Captains Chair Straight Leg Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the captain's chair with your back against the backrest and your forearms resting on the arm pads. | Step:2 Keep your upper body stable and your back straight. | Step:3 Engage your abs and lift your legs up in front of you, keeping them straight. | Step:4 Continue lifting until your legs are parallel to the ground or as high as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pelvic Tilt
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands by your sides. | Step:3 Engage your abs and tilt your pelvis upward, pressing your lower back into the ground. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, focusing on contracting your abs. | Step:5 Release the tilt and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Quarter Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Elbow-To-Knee
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engage your abs and lift your upper body off the ground, bringing your right elbow towards your left knee. | Step:4 At the same time, bring your left knee towards your right elbow, creating a twisting motion. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body and extend your legs back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the movement, this time bringing your left elbow towards your right knee and your right knee towards your left elbow. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hanging Straight Leg Hip Raise
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up in front of you until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Russian Twist
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Lean back slightly while keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Hold your hands together in front of your chest or hold a weight if desired. | Step:4 Lift your feet off the ground, balancing on your sit bones. | Step:5 Twist your torso to the right, bringing your hands or weight towards the right side of your body. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then twist your torso to the left, bringing your hands or weight towards the left side of your body. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying Leg-Hip Raise - Contracted Variation
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Place your hands under your glutes for support. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your legs off the ground, raising them towards the ceiling. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. Emphasize contracted control. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hanging Straight Leg Raise With Elevated
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up in front of you, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Continue lifting until your legs are parallel to the ground or as high as you can comfortably go. Maintain elevated form throughout. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sit-Up With Arms On Chest With Mini
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Cross your arms over your chest. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your upper body off the ground towards your knees. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. Maintain mini form throughout. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying Leg Raise Flat Bench
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a flat bench with your back pressed against it. | Step:2 Place your hands under your glutes for support. | Step:3 Keep your legs straight and together, and lift them up towards the ceiling. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Seated Leg Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat bench with your back straight and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands on the sides of the bench for support. | Step:3 Keeping your legs straight, slowly raise them up in front of you until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying Leg-Hip Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Place your hands under your glutes for support. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your legs off the ground, raising them towards the ceiling. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: V-Sit On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Lean back slightly and lift your legs off the ground, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Simultaneously, lift your upper body off the ground and reach your arms towards your legs. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, then slowly lower your upper body and legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hanging Leg Raise
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up in front of you, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Continue lifting until your legs are parallel to the ground or as high as you can comfortably go. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sit-Up With Arms On Chest
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Cross your arms over your chest. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your upper body off the ground towards your knees. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Alternate Heel Touchers
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out to the sides, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your shoulders off the ground and reach your right hand towards your right heel. | Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat on the left side, reaching your left hand towards your left heel. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sit-Up V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Jackknife Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms overhead. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs and upper body simultaneously, reaching your hands towards your toes. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs and upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hanging Oblique Knee Raise
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your knees towards your chest, twisting your torso to the side as you do so. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat on the other side, twisting your torso in the opposite direction. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: L-Sit On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Place your hands on the floor beside your hips, fingers pointing forward. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your legs off the ground, keeping them straight. | Step:4 Try to bring your legs parallel to the floor, forming an 'L' shape with your body. | Step:5 Hold this position for as long as you can. | Step:6 Slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Flexion Leg Sit Up (Bent Knee)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 At the same time, lift your legs off the ground, bending your knees and bringing them towards your chest. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body and legs back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hanging Straight Leg Raise
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up in front of you, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Continue lifting until your legs are parallel to the ground or as high as you can comfortably go. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Twisting Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet secured under the foot pads. | Step:3 Place your hands behind your head or across your chest. | Step:4 Engage your abs and lift your upper body off the bench, curling forward. | Step:5 As you curl up, twist your torso to one side, bringing your elbow towards the opposite knee. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat the movement, this time twisting your torso to the other side. | Step:8 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing Pelvic Tilt
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Place your hands on your hips or let them hang by your sides. | Step:3 Engage your core muscles and tilt your pelvis forward, pushing your lower back towards the wall behind you. | Step:4 Hold the position for a few seconds, then release and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: 45° Side Bend
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended straight down by your sides. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, slowly bend your torso to one side, lowering your hand towards your knee. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat on the other side. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Vertical Leg Raise (On Parallel Bars)
instructions: Step:1 Hang from the parallel bars with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up in front of you, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Continue lifting until your legs are parallel to the ground or slightly higher. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Prisoner Half Sit-Up (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Firm Style Hanging Oblique Knee Raise
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your knees towards your chest, twisting your torso to the side as you do so. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat on the other side, twisting your torso in the opposite direction. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions. Emphasize firm control.
